      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Data storage",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Data storage",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3ClCSG5irB4UxdqGpZzr1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2387.75227596522,
      "y": 361.802552759425,
      "width": 732.5995483398438,
      "height": 650,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 888920242,
      "version": 606,
      "versionNonce": 832808626,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782701641287,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We want to store messages\nOptions:\n1. DB\n2. WAL\n\nWe want storage optimised for read and write\nSQL : optimised for read\nNoSQL : optimised for writes\n\nNone works for us\n\nWAL: Write ahead log\ngood on sequencial access\nso good for writes and if reads are sequnecial\ngood for them.\n\nStore data in files known as segments. segment file is of certain threshold\nnew file gets created.\ndata is written in latest segment file\n\nSo we go ahead with WAL\nWe write data sequencially at offset\n\nConsumers maintain an offset where they read data seuencially\n\none partition cant be consumed by ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We want to store messages\nOptions:\n1. DB\n2. WAL\n\nWe want storage optimised for read and write\nSQL : optimised for read\nNoSQL : optimised for writes\n\nNone works for us\n\nWAL: Write ahead log\ngood on sequencial access\nso good for writes and if reads are sequnecial\ngood for them.\n\nStore data in files known as segments. segment file is of certain threshold\nnew file gets created.\ndata is written in latest segment file\n\nSo we go ahead with WAL\nWe write data sequencially at offset\n\nConsumers maintain an offset where they read data seuencially\n\none partition cant be consumed by ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "LRH_AVaSjs4rgB9dPnG2B",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2406.212050564305,
      "y": 1041.4394299611718,
      "width": 917.4392700195312,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bJN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1211289902,
      "version": 242,
      "versionNonce": 1758778734,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782701641287,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. Message Data structure\n\nMessage:\nmessage_id UUID\ntopic String\npartition_id integer\noffset integer\nkey byte[]\nvalue byte[]\ntimestamp TIMEUUID\nsize Integer\ncrc  integer ( Cyclic Redundancy Check (CRC) is a technique used to detect accidental errors)\ntags string[]",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. Message Data structure\n\nMessage:\nmessage_id UUID\ntopic String\npartition_id integer\noffset integer\nkey byte[]\nvalue byte[]\ntimestamp TIMEUUID\nsize Integer\ncrc  integer ( Cyclic Redundancy Check (CRC) is a technique used to detect accidental errors)\ntags string[]",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
