    },
    {
      "id": "70uVnwbLGtQ8qxcHKi0oJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2328.6647411920385,
      "y": 965.8732606269027,
      "width": 1102.2071533203125,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRI",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1269777198,
      "version": 26,
      "versionNonce": 1002082862,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782731682381,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Other optimisations\n2. Feed Truncation\n\nMost users only view the first few dozen posts. Systems often precompute and cache only the top N \n(for example, 500–1000) posts in a user's feed. Older posts are fetched lazily when the user scrolls deeper.\n\n3. Batch Fan-out\n\nInstead of updating millions of feeds synchronously, fan-out workers process follower lists in batches \n(e.g., 1,000 followers per job), improving throughput and allowing retries without blocking post creation.\n\n4. Eventual Consistency\n\nFeeds are typically eventually consistent. A newly published post may take a few seconds to appear for some \nfollowers because asynchronous fan-out, cache updates, and ranking pipelines prioritize availability and scalability over immediate consistency.\n\n5. Cold Start\n\nFor new users with few or no follows, candidate generation relies on:\n\nTrending posts\nPopular creators\nLocation-specific content\nInterest-based recommendations inferred from onboarding\nSponsored content",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Other optimisations\n2. Feed Truncation\n\nMost users only view the first few dozen posts. Systems often precompute and cache only the top N \n(for example, 500–1000) posts in a user's feed. Older posts are fetched lazily when the user scrolls deeper.\n\n3. Batch Fan-out\n\nInstead of updating millions of feeds synchronously, fan-out workers process follower lists in batches \n(e.g., 1,000 followers per job), improving throughput and allowing retries without blocking post creation.\n\n4. Eventual Consistency\n\nFeeds are typically eventually consistent. A newly published post may take a few seconds to appear for some \nfollowers because asynchronous fan-out, cache updates, and ranking pipelines prioritize availability and scalability over immediate consistency.\n\n5. Cold Start\n\nFor new users with few or no follows, candidate generation relies on:\n\nTrending posts\nPopular creators\nLocation-specific content\nInterest-based recommendations inferred from onboarding\nSponsored content",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Nu0myDrf6v1Jk4BeaH0sl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3576.1378809300368,
      "y": 329.2095079626922,
      "width": 517.423583984375,
      "height": 800,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1127918386,
      "version": 28,
      "versionNonce": 5260658,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782731743780,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "End to end flow\n\nUser A\n  │\n  │ POST /posts\n  ▼\nAPI Gateway\n  │\n  ▼\nPost Service\n  │\n  ├── Store metadata (DB)\n  ├── Upload media (Object Store)\n  └── Publish PostCreated\n           │\n           ▼\n         Kafka\n           │\n   ┌───────┴────────┐\n   │                │\n   ▼                ▼\nFan-out Service   Search Indexer\n   │\n   ├── Normal user? → Push PostID into followers' feed caches\n   └── Celebrity? → Skip push (handled on read)\n           │\n           ▼\nUser B opens Home Feed\n           │\n           ▼\nFeed Service\n           │\n   ├── Read cached PostIDs\n   ├── Fetch celebrity posts\n   ├── Retrieve post metadata\n   ├── Apply visibility, mute, and block filters\n   ├── Generate additional recommendation candidates\n   ├── Rank candidates\n   ├── Insert ads\n   └── Return cursor + posts",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "End to end flow\n\nUser A\n  │\n  │ POST /posts\n  ▼\nAPI Gateway\n  │\n  ▼\nPost Service\n  │\n  ├── Store metadata (DB)\n  ├── Upload media (Object Store)\n  └── Publish PostCreated\n           │\n           ▼\n         Kafka\n           │\n   ┌───────┴────────┐\n   │                │\n   ▼                ▼\nFan-out Service   Search Indexer\n   │\n   ├── Normal user? → Push PostID into followers' feed caches\n   └── Celebrity? → Skip push (handled on read)\n           │\n           ▼\nUser B opens Home Feed\n           │\n           ▼\nFeed Service\n           │\n   ├── Read cached PostIDs\n   ├── Fetch celebrity posts\n   ├── Retrieve post metadata\n   ├── Apply visibility, mute, and block filters\n   ├── Generate additional recommendation candidates\n   ├── Rank candidates\n   ├── Insert ads\n   └── Return cursor + posts",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
